# Cloud Functions Conventions

## SDK Version
Always use **v2 SDK**. Never use the deprecated v1 API.

```js
// ✅ Correct
const { onCall, HttpsError } = require('firebase-functions/v2/https');
const { setGlobalOptions } = require('firebase-functions/v2');

// ❌ Wrong — v1 deprecated API
const functions = require('firebase-functions');
functions.runWith({ ... }).https.onCall(...)
```

## Secrets
API keys are stored as Firebase secrets, passed via the `secrets` option:
```js
exports.hobbyQuiz = onCall(
  { secrets: ['GEMINI_API_KEY'] },
  async (request) => {
    const apiKey = process.env.GEMINI_API_KEY;
    // ...
  }
);
```

Never hardcode keys. Never read from `.env` in Cloud Functions.

## Gemini API Pattern
Use the REST API directly via axios:
```js
const url = `https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models/${model}:generateContent?key=${apiKey}`;
const body = {
  contents,
  generationConfig: { temperature, maxOutputTokens },
  systemInstruction: systemText ? { parts: [{ text: systemText }] } : undefined,
};
```

### Model Selection
| Feature | Model | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Quiz recommendations | `gemini-2.5-flash` | Reliable structured JSON |
| Coach chat | `gemini-2.5-flash` | Fast conversational reasoning |
| Tutorial summarization | `gemini-2.5-flash-lite` | Lighter task, lower cost |

> Gemini model IDs get retired periodically (e.g. `gemini-2.0-flash*` shut down June 1, 2026). If Cloud Functions start returning `500` with an `AxiosError 404` from `generativelanguage.googleapis.com`, check the [Gemini API changelog](https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/changelog) for the current model ID.

## Gemini Message Format
- Gemini requires alternating `user`/`model` turns
- Map `assistant` → `model` role
- Merge consecutive same-role messages
- Conversation must start with a `user` message
- Use `buildGeminiContents()` helper in `functions/index.js`

## Auth
All callable functions should verify `request.auth`:
```js
if (!request.auth) {
  throw new HttpsError('unauthenticated', 'Must be logged in');
}
```

## JSON Output from AI
When expecting structured JSON from Gemini:
1. Prompt with "Return ONLY valid JSON with no markdown"
2. Clean response: `raw.replace(/```json|```/g, '').trim()`
3. Parse with `JSON.parse(cleaned)`
4. Validate shape before returning
